<bug>
    <id>160907</id>
    <title>Ecore default editor context menu shows inappropriate items</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Inherited from other activities, such as: Run As.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">, Debug As.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.5">, etc..</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.6">See the following GMF report for same issue and a solution.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=152453</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">A simpler solution may be to remove the following line from the generated [Model]Editor.createContextMenuFor(.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">.)</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">getSite().</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">registerContextMenu(contextMenu, viewer);</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">That works for me but I don't know whether it has unintended consquences.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">Also, validate, Load Resource.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.3">.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.4">, and so on are then not removed.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.5">It is not clear to me wether these more generic EMF solutions are appropriate for the non-root ecore elements.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
